# Deliberately non-identifiable toy for FIM identifiability tests (GH #202).
#
# A --keff--> B with keff = k1 + k2 a derived (ConstantExpression) rate
# constant. Because A depends on k1 and k2 ONLY through their sum, the output
# sensitivities obey dA/dk1 == dA/dk2 at every time point, so the Fisher
# Information Matrix over (k1, k2) is rank-1: the [1, -1] eigen-direction has a
# zero eigenvalue (practically non-identifiable / sloppy). Only the sum k1+k2
# is identifiable from the trajectory.
begin parameters
    1 k1    0.05  # Constant
    2 k2    0.05  # Constant
    3 keff  k1+k2  # ConstantExpression
end parameters
begin species
    1 A() 100
    2 B() 0
end species
begin reactions
    1 1 2 keff  #_R1
end reactions
begin groups
    1 A_tot 1
    2 B_tot 2
end groups
